Class RDBQRY

java.lang.Object
  tokyotyrant.RDBQRY

public class RDBQRY
extends java.lang.Object

Query is a mechanism to search for and retrieve records corresponding conditions from table database.

Method Detail

addcond

public void addcond(java.lang.String name,
                    int op,
                    java.lang.String expr)
Add a narrowing condition.

Parameters:
name - the name of a column. An empty string means the primary key.
op - an operation type: `RDBQRY.QCSTREQ' for string which is equal to the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTRINC' for string which is included in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTRBW' for string which begins with the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTREW' for string which ends with the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTRAND' for string which includes all tokens in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTROR' for string which includes at least one token in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTROREQ' for string which is equal to at least one token in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCSTRRX' for string which matches regular expressions of the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMEQ' for number which is equal to the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMGT' for number which is greater than the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMGE' for number which is greater than or equal to the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMLT' for number which is less than the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMLE' for number which is less than or equal to the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMBT' for number which is between two tokens of the expression, `RDBQRY.QCNUMOREQ' for number which is equal to at least one token in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCFTSPH' for full-text search with the phrase of the expression, `RDBQRY.QCFTSAND' for full-text search with all tokens in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCFTSOR' for full-text search with at least one token in the expression, `RDBQRY.QCFTSEX' for full-text search with the compound expression. All operations can be flagged by bitwise-or: `RDBQRY.QCNEGATE' for negation, `RDBQRY.QCNOIDX' for using no index.
expr - an operand exression.

metasearch

public java.util.List metasearch(RDBQRY[] others,
                                 int type)
Retrieve records with multiple query objects and get the set of the result.

Parameters:
others - an array of the query objects except for the self object.
type - a set operation type: `RDBQRY.MSUNION' for the union set, `RDBQRY.MSISECT' for the intersection set, `RDBQRY.MSDIFF' for the difference set. If it is not defined, `RDBQRY.MSUNION' is specified.
Returns:
a list object of the primary keys of the corresponding records. This method does never fail. It returns an empty array even if no record corresponds.
Note:
If the first query object has the order setting, the result array is sorted by the order.

search

public java.util.List search()
Execute the search.

Returns:
a list object of the primary keys of the corresponding records. This method does never fail. It returns an empty array even if no record corresponds.

searchout

public boolean searchout()
Remove each corresponding record.

Returns:
If successful, the return value is true, else, it is false.

setlimit

public void setlimit(int max,
                     int skip)
Set the maximum number of records of the result.

Parameters:
max - the maximum number of records of the result. If it is negative, no limit is specified.
skip - the maximum number of records of the result. If it is not more than 0, no record is skipped.

setorder

public void setorder(java.lang.String name,
                     int type)
Set the order of the result.

Parameters:
name - the name of a column. An empty string means the primary key.
type - the order type: `RDBQRY.QOSTRASC' for string ascending, `RDBQRY.QOSTRDESC' for string descending, `RDBQRY.QONUMASC' for number ascending, `RDBQRY.QONUMDESC' for number descending.
